                            1 => array(
                                'name' => 'Tool Proficiencies',
                                'text' => 'One type of gaming set',
                            ),
                            2 => array(
                                'name' => 'Languages',
                                'text' => 'One of your choice',
                            ),
                            3 => array(
                                'name' => 'Equipment',
                                'text' => 'A banner or other token from a noble lord or lady to whom you have given your heart, a set of fine clothes, a signet ring, a scroll of pedigree, and a purse containing 25 gp',
                            ),
                            4 => array(
                                'name' => 'Feature: Retainers',
                                'text' => 'You have the service of three retainers loyal to your family. These retainers can be attendants or messengers, and one might be a majordomo. One of your retainers is a noble who serves as your squire, aiding you in exchange for training on his or her own path to knighthood. Your two remaining retainers might include a groom to care for your horse and a servant who polishes your armor (and even helps you put it on).

Your retainers (2 commoners, 1 noble) can perform mundane tasks for you, but they do not fight for you, will not follow you into obviously dangerous areas (such as dungeons), and will leave if they are frequently endangered or abused.',
                            ),
                        ),
                    ),
